HEADWORD: Mycelium
<hw>My*ce"li*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<grk>my`khs</grk> a mushroom.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The white
threads or filamentous growth from which a mushroom or fungus is
developed; the so-called mushroom spawn.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>My*ce"li*al</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

